      • selectModuleInstance

        @PublishedMethod
void selectModuleInstance(AsrPath moduleConfig)
        Selects a module instance for execution.
        If there are multiple module configuration instances associated with an generator this method can be used to select specific ones.
        It is possible to pass full qualified path (E.g. AsrPath.create("/ActiveEcuC/CanInst1") ).
        Previous selections are not cleared by this method.
        If no module configurations are selected, all available are executed.
        Parameters:
        moduleConfig - the AsrPath of the module config

      • selectModuleInstance

        @PublishedMethod
void selectModuleInstance(java.lang.String moduleConfig)
        Selects a module instance for execution.
        If there are multiple module configuration instances associated with an generator this method can be used to select specific ones.
        It is possible to pass full qualified path (E.g. "/ActiveEcuC/CanInst1") or only the short name of the module configuration (E.g. "CanInst1").
        Previous selections are not cleared by this method.
        If no module configurations are selected, all available are executed.
        Parameters:
        moduleConfig - the path of the module config

      • setReadOnly

        @KeepSecretFromPublishedApi
void setReadOnly()
        Sets the current Object to read only. If read only is enabled, changes on this object result in an IllegalStateException.
        The read only state is applied recursively to all child settings.
